  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0d9a \u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0d85\u0dc3\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dab\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "It is unfair to increase fares when there are no buses",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Gemunu Wijeratne, President of the Private Bus Owners' Association, said that the increase in bus fares was unjust at a time when 90 percent of private buses could not run.",
        "He said the government had increased fuel prices when there was no fuel in the country and had also increased bus fares when buses were not running. He also said that such a government was of no use to the country.",
        "Mr. Wijeratne said that what is currently in effect is an increased bus fare to transport passengers to the number of seats during the covid epidemic. Mr. Wijeratne said that now the passenger who hangs on the roof and behind the buses also has to pay the seat fare.",
        "He said that although there was nothing wrong with implementing the national policy of increasing bus fares, it would be more appropriate to postpone the implementation of the increase in fares until at least 75 percent of the buses have started running.",
        "Looking at the current situation, there is a lot of disappointment and the bus industry may face problems if the minimum bus fare is increased to 40 rupees by encouraging many passengers to walk that distance, the chairman said that he has now thought of going to the struggle ground."
      ],
